resources.string: "When TalkBack is on, your device provides spoken feedback to help blind and low-vision users. For example, it describes what you touch, select and activate.\n\nIf you have turned TalkBack on accidentally, turn it off by tapping the switch until the green outline is around it, then double-tapping it. Do the same interaction for the resulting confirmation dialogue."
"There are currently no customised labels. You can create one by navigating to an unlabelled image and then adding a label from the Local Context Menu."
"Swipe with two fingers to switch pages."
"Touch the screen and explore in a circle to find an item, then lift to activate."
"Touch the screen and explore in a circle to navigate on-screen content, then lift to focus."
"Notifications are spoken when the screen is off"
"No speech occurs when the screen is off"
"Phonetic letters will be spoken when long pressing on the keyboard and moving the accessibility focus by a character."
"Usage hints won\'t be spoken when moving accessibility focus."
"Usage hints will be spoken during navigation, after a brief delay."
"(Experimental) Tap on currently focused item to activate"
"TalkBack will reset keymap and change modifier key to %1$s"
"Press key combination to set new shortcut. It must contain at least ALT or Control key."
"Press key combination with %1$s modifier key to set new shortcut."
"Press Backspace to clear the shortcut, press Enter to save or press Escape to cancel."
"Are you sure that you would like to reset your shortcut keys for this keymap to their default values? Please note that this action cannot be undone."
"This key combination is used for \'%1$s\' action. Do you want to clear it and assign this shortcut to \'%2$s\'?"
"Speak keyboard feedback in a lower-pitched voice"
"TalkBack accessibility service has dimmed the screen."
"Undo by pressing Volume Up and Volume Down keys together three times quickly."
"Screen dim can be controlled from TalkBack Settings."
"Tap to review changes to accessibility gestures"

"Are you sure? Your device will not provide feedback and Explore by Touch will be disabled. You can resume TalkBack from notifications, by returning to the lock screen, or through the volume key shortcut."
"You can resume TalkBack from the notifications shade."
"You can resume TalkBack from the notifications shade or by turning the screen on."
"You can resume TalkBack from the notifications shade or by returning to the lock screen."
"Enter the text to be used for this image in the field below."
"Are you sure that you want to remove the \"%1$s\" label?"
"Are you sure that you want to remove the \"%1$s\" label within %2$s?"
"Choose whether you want to override or skip existing labels in the case of conflict."
"Nothing to export. You have not added any labels"

"This version of TalkBack includes changes to the default accessibility gestures. The actions associated with these gestures can be customised within TalkBack settings. When Explore by touch is enabled, you can use the following gestures to perform certain actions.\n\n%1$s"
"Long press volume up and down keys"
"Press both volume keys three times quickly to enable or disable screen dimming"
"Are you sure you want to dim the screen?"

"This version of TalkBack includes changes to the default accessibility gestures.

The up-then-down gesture will allow you to move to the first item on the screen, and the down-then-up gesture will move to the last item.

The reading granularity can now be changed by focusing an item, then selecting a granularity from the local context menu.

You can change the actions performed by these gestures in TalkBack Settings."

"This version of TalkBack includes changes to the default accessibility gestures.\n\nThe \'up\' gesture now moves to the previous navigation setting, and the \'down\' gesture now moves to the next navigation setting."
"Are you sure that you want to turn off Explore by touch?\n\nYour device will no longer respond to shortcut gestures or speak items when you touch the screen."
"Are you sure that you want to turn on node tree debugging?\n\nNode tree debugging exposes the content of your screen to your device\'s logs, which may be read by other applications."
"Explore by touch is not available in web content. Turn on %1$s in Accessibility settings to explore web content."
"Permission to send gestures to TalkBack and resume spoken feedback."
"Permission to access, modify and delete customised labels spoken by TalkBack."
"Press arrow buttons to change value, or press select to finish."
"Press %1$s to see the list of shortcuts"
"For best results with touch and spoken feedback, maximise the app window"
